The paper discusses a technique for improving the efficiency of fuzzing, which is a technique for finding software vulnerabilities. This falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) and computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes the use of neural network models, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses the use of gradient-guided optimization, which involves the use of derivatives, and thus falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
